{{Infobox waterfall | photo = Quarry Falls (Macon County, North Carolina).JPG | photo_caption = Quarry Falls in Summer | name = Quarry Falls | location = [[Macon County, NC|Macon County]], [[North Carolina]] | type = Cascade | height = | drop = | numberofdrops = | flow = | coords = {{coord|35.0924|-83.2670}} }}
'''Quarry Falls''' is a small [[waterfall]] (or perhaps large rapid in high water) located beside US Hwy. 64 west of [[Highlands, North Carolina|Highlands]], [[North Carolina]], [[United States]]. It is best known for the large, deep pool at the bottom and is a popular place for swimming during warm weather. Quarry Falls is known to the locals as "Bust-Your-Butt-Falls" or "Sliding Rock".
==Nearby Falls== *[[Dry Falls (Macon County)|Dry Falls]] *[[Cullasaja Falls]] *[[Bridal Veil Falls (Macon County)|Bridal Veil Falls]]
